CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1774019481
OL,3,CUnite boss joins Birmingham bin worker
OL,4,Crally as strikes pass one year mark
OL,6,F"The council should now honour the
OL,7,Fdeal scoped out at Acas and stop
OL,8,Fwasting millions of pounds of
OL,9,Fresidents' money on failed attempts to
OL,10,Fbreak the strike.
OL,12,F"Workers and communities should not be
OL,13,Fpaying the price for the clear
OL,14,Ffailings of the council's management."
OL,16,FLast week on the anniversary of the
OL,17,Fall-out strike beginning, Unite's
OL,18,Fexecutive council voted to cut its
OL,19,Faffiliation fee to Labour by 40%
OL,20,F(#580,000) in protest against the
OL,21,Fparty's stance on the dispute.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUvD@fO]
